Question: Do you think it is ok for the government to read your emails for counter-terrorism purposes?
Answer:
I do not think so. Indeed counter-terrorism is an important task but the privacy of people is also critical. I do not think reading emails can help a lot in counter terrorism. Terrorists will probably communicate via phone or talk face to face instead. If we allow government to read our email, next step will be the phone, mail and we will have no privacy at all.